Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
placePipeline(25.10)                                      placePipeline(25.10)

Name
       placePipeline  -  Places  the registers of the specified pipeline flip-
       flops (PFF) net group(s) so that the distances between  the  stages  of
       each group are roughly equal

Syntax
       placePipeline

       [-netGroup {<netGroupName>}]

       [-region {true | false }]

       [-status {fixed | placed}

       [-timingBased]

       [-utilization <utilization_value>]

       Places  the  registers  of  the specified pipeline flip-flops (PFF) net
       group(s) so that the distances between the stages  of  each  group  are
       roughly  equal. This command can be used if the pipeline net groups are
       specified in the design.

Parameters
       -netGroup {<netGroupName>}
              Specifies the PFF net group, or a list of net groups, to  place.
              By default, all PFF net groups in design are considered.

       -region {true | false}
              Creates  region constraints for flops in each stage of pipeline,
              to allow adjustments at a later stage.

              Default: false

       -status {fixed | placed}
              Places the PFFs with fixed placement status, or placed status.

              Default: placed

       -timingBased
              Automatically finds reserve  lengths.  The  option  is  of  type
              boolean and is optional.

       -utilization <utilization_value>
              Specifies the expected utilization of regions for flops.

              Minimum: 0

              Maximum: 1

              Note: The -region option is required with the -utilization.

Example
              * The  following  command  places  the registers of all pipeline
                flip-flops (PFF) net groups at equal distance:

                placePipeline

              * The following command places the registers of  pipeline  flip-
                flops  (PFF)  net  group named netGroup1 at equal distance and
                marked the registers status FIXED:

                placePipeline -netGroup netGroup1 -status fixed

Related Information
